                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1182">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-18T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1912—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In view of the presence of the large number of Americans, foreigners, and
                    noncombatants in Vera Cruz, and their important interests there, and the
                    difficulty, if not the impossibility, of their being able to protect themselves,
                    you are directed to say to the Foreign Office that the Department hopes that no
                    fighting, either in the streets of Vera Cruz or elsewhere which would seriously
                    endanger the persons and interests referred to, will take place.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
